  "intent_precise": "Pierce NiNTA Magnetic Beads Part 1: Using equilibration buffer (reservoir, slot 4), beads (tuberack, slot 5), mag_rack (deep_well_plate, slot 4), samples (deep_well_plate, slot 7). With magnetic module. (1) Transfer from source to destination. (2) Transfer from source to destination. (3) Transfer from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (4) Disengage magnets to release beads. (5) Mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L. (6) Mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L. (7) Transfer 250\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Mix 5 times. (9) Transfer from source to destination. (10) Engage magnets at 4.2mm height for bead separation. (11) Incubate for 2 minutes. (12) Disengage magnets to release beads. (13) Mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L. (14) Engage magnets at 4.2mm height for bead separation. (15) Incubate for 2 minutes. (16) Disengage magnets to release beads. (17) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (18) Mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L. (19) Pause: 30 min gentle shaking, room temp",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 50\u00b5L-250\u00b5L, ~5 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Pierce NiNTA magnetic bead preparation, start by setting up your equilibration buffer in reservoir slot 4, beads in tuberack slot 5, and samples in the deep well plate at slot 7, with your magnetic rack positioned at slot 4. Begin the protocol by transferring materials between the designated wells, then disengage the magnets and mix the beads 5 times at 250\u00b5L volume twice before transferring 250\u00b5L to your destination and mixing 5 more times. Next, engage the magnets at 4.2mm height for bead separation and incubate for 2 minutes, then disengage and mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L, followed by another magnetic separation cycle at 4.2mm height with 2-minute incubation. Finally, disengage the magnets, transfer from source A1 to destination A1, mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L, and pause the protocol for 30 minutes of gentle shaking at room temperature.",
